ror`.\\n- `SecuritySupport4Test` passed in the same native run, which shows `javax.activation.SecuritySupport#getSystemResources(\\\"META-INF/mimetypes.default\\\")` could still find classpath resources in the image.\\n- Codex had already tried resource-related support for `META-INF/mimetypes.default`, so the remaining problem was not an unresolved missing resource registration.\\n\\nRoot cause:\\n\\n- `SecuritySupport2Test` depends on a generated test resource overriding the library's built-in `META-INF/mimetypes.default` so that `MimetypesFileTypeMap` resolves `sample.securitysupport2` to `text/x-securitysupport2`.\\n- The implementation dependency `com.sun.activation:javax.activation:1.2.0` already ships its own `META-INF/mimetypes.default`.\\n- In Native Image, the generated override was not the resource actually consumed by `MimetypesFileTypeMap`, so the lookup fell back to the default mapping and returned `application/octet-stream`.\\n- That is a duplicate-resource / resource-selection behavior issue in this test scenario, not missing reachability metadata for the library API.\\n\\n## Action taken\\n\\nRemoved the non-metadata failing generated test and its test-only support:\\n\\n- deleted `tests/src/javax.activation/javax.activation-api/1.2.0/src/test/java/javax_activation/javax_activation_api/SecuritySupport2Test.java`\\n- deleted `tests/src/javax.activation/javax.activation-api/1.2.0/src/test/resources/META-INF/mimetypes.default`\\n- removed the extra test-jar packaging block from `tests/src/javax.activation/javax.activation-api/1.2.0/build.gradle`\\n\\n## Why the remaining generated support should be preserved\\n\\nThe remaining generated support still covers meaningful native-image behaviors for this library and should stay in place:\\n\\n- `CommandInfoBeansTest` exercises `CommandInfo` instantiation through the Beans API.\\n- `MailcapCommandMapTest` exercises dynamic handler loading and fallback class loading paths.\\n- `SecuritySupport4Test` still vali